Governor Bello Mohammed Matawalle of Zamfara state has urged security
agencies to concentrate more on the state in the fight against banditry as Zamfara is now the epicentre of the banditry. Speaking while receiving the Inspector-General of Police (IGP), Mohammed Adamu, at the Government House in Gusau, Matawalle said majority of the bandits terrorising innocent citizens have their homes in the state. According to him, for the fight against bandits to be successful, attention should be given to the territory of the Zamfara state even as he tasked security agencies on proper coordination. “There is need for proper coordination amongst the security agencies
in the fight against banditry,” he said. He reiterated the resolve of his administration to extend all
required support to the security agencies to fight bandits in the
state. In his response, IGP Adamu said he was in the state in obedience to the
presidential directive to come down and assess the situation on the
ground. He stressed that President Muhammadu Buhari was so concerned about the security situation in the country and is determined to put an end to it.